The paper deals with the problem of distributed computing by mobile robots, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of multiple sub-fields in computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), which focuses on the study of systems composed of multiple interacting agents, such as robots. The second most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics), which deals with the design, construction, and operation of robots. The third most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), which deals with the design and analysis of algorithms and systems for distributed computing. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which deals with the study of algorithms and data structures. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and control of complex systems, such as mobile robot systems.
